val sch = StructType.fromDDL("""ts string,
 elb_name string,
 request_ip string,
 backend_ip string,
 request_processing_time double,
 backend_processing_time double,
 client_response_time double,
 elb_response_code string,
 backend_response_code string,
 received_bytes bigint,
 sent_bytes bigint,
 request string,
 user_agent string,
 ssl_cipher string,
 ssl_protocol string""")

val raw_data = spark.read.schema(sch).option("delimiter"," ").csv("s3://paytmviny/inp_data/2015_07_22_mktplace_shop_web_log_sample.log.gz")

val wndw = Window.partitionBy("clientip").orderBy($"ts")

/*
    val std_data = raw_data.select(
      $"ts".as("ts_string"),
      regexp_replace($"ts","T"," ").as("ts_str_new"),
      unix_timestamp($"ts", "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss").cast("timestamp").as("ts_timestamp"),
      $"ts".cast("timestamp").as("ts_dir_timestamp"),

      // date_format($"ts".cast("timestamp"), "yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss").cast("timestamp").as("ts_new"),
      // split($"request_ip",":")(0).as("clientip"),split($"request"," ")(1).as("url"),
      $"elb_response_code")
*/
                       /*
Converting the timestamp values to only have information until seconds(yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss),
    since i think it was not necessary to use microseconds when evaluating sessions time.
    Also extracted IP and excluded the ports from request_ip column
    Extracted only the URL from request.
    Using lag functions populated a column :prevts for every client, will use this for generating sessionid later
    Also generated a new column called timediff which will have the time difference(in mins) for every client between their two
    consecutive occurences.Thier first apperance record will have a 0. Casted this to Decimal(12,4). Had faced precsion issues with
    double and also using lower precision of decimal.
*/ 

 val std_data = raw_data.select(
                                  //date_format($"ts".cast("timestamp"), "yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss").cast("timestamp").as("ts"),
                                // unix_timestamp($"ts", "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss").cast("timestamp").as("ts"),
                                  $"ts".cast("timestamp").as("ts"),
                                 split($"request_ip",":")(0).as("clientip"),
                                  split($"request"," ")(1).as("url"),
                                  $"elb_response_code")
                           .withColumn("prevts", lag($"ts",1).over(wndw))
                           .withColumn("timediff", when($"prevts".isNull,0).otherwise(($"ts".cast("decimal(18,6)") - $"prevts".cast("decimal(18,6)"))/60.0).cast("decimal(38,10)"))

//Same as above but in ascending order
sessioned_data.groupBy($"sessionid",$"clientip").agg(count($"*").as("cnt")).orderBy($"cnt".asc).show()

// AVG SESSION TIME Per Client
sessioned_data.groupBy($"sessionid",$"clientip")
              .agg(((max($"ts").cast("decimal(18,6)")-min($"ts").cast("decimal(18,6)"))/60.0).cast("decimal(18,6)").as("sessiontime"))
              .groupBy($"clientip")
              .agg(avg($"sessiontime").as("avgsessionperclient(in mins)"), count($"*").as("numsessionperclient")).orderBy($"avgsessionperclient(in mins)".desc).show()

//Users who are most engaged based on session time
sessioned_data.groupBy($"sessionid",$"clientip")
              .agg(((max($"ts").cast("decimal(18,6)")-min($"ts").cast("decimal(18,6)"))/60.0).cast("decimal(18,6)").as("sessiontime"),
                    min($"ts").as("session_starttime"),max($"ts").as("session_endtime"))
              .orderBy($"sessiontime".desc).show(100,false)

/*
Rangebin 0 - Number of session where session time is 0 mins ie basically user was seen only once in a session.We have such 22192 sessions 
Rangebin 1 - User spent between > 0 and <=2.0 mins . We have such 66045 sessions
Rangebin 2 - User spent between > 2 and <=4.0 mins . We have such 15239 sessions
Rangebin 3 - User spent between > 4 and <=6.0 mins . We have such 3387 sessions
and so on ...
*/
sessioned_data.groupBy($"sessionid",$"clientip")
              .agg(((max($"ts").cast("decimal(18,6)")-min($"ts").cast("decimal(18,6)"))/60.0).cast("decimal(18,6)").as("sessiontime"))
              .groupBy(ceil($"sessiontime"/2.0).as("rangebin")).count().orderBy($"rangebin").show(false)
